significant positive relationship between the ridge-to-pit ratio and p63 
population density (r=0.85) and the ridge-to-pit ratio and CK-5/6 intensity 
(r=0.63).
CONCLUSIONS: Molecular changes related to epithelial progressive maturation and 
cellular proliferation are correlated with concomitant alteration of epithelial 
surface architecture which helps to predict the malignant potentiality of OSF.

